SEC. 9.

Qualifications for examination.

âIn order to be admitted to the dental hygienist examination, an applicant must, before admission thereto, establish to the satisfaction of the Board thatâ

He is a citizen of the Philippines;

He is at least eighteen years of age;

He is of good moral character and reputation;

He is not suffering from any contagious disease and is physically fit to perform services as a dental hygienist;

He had finished a standard four-year high school nurse or its equivalent in a school recognized by the government; and

He had graduated with the title of graduate dental hygienist (G.D.H.) or its equivalent, after completing a dental hygienist course of at least two years and of a. standard or scope duly approved by the Board from a legally incorporated dental college or university, dental infirmary, or any other institution of equal standing, duly accredited and recognized by the government.
